package com.keepitsimple.java;

public class StaticAndNonStatic {
public static void main(String[] args) {
	System.out.println("Within the main method ...");
	
	/*Let me explain about the modifiers 
	1. Access 2. Non-access Modifiers
	1. Access -> Private (Only within the class), Protected (Only within the package provoided classes should have IS-A)
	Default (Only within the package No need of IS-A), Public (Anywhere)
	2. Non-access -> Static, Synchronized, Transient, Abstract, Volatile, Final, Native etc..
	Note : All of these are key words and should be used with the lowercase just for the explaination I have written in a proper english way*/ 
	
/*	Static : Any thing which belongs to an entire class 
	Non-static : which is specific to the specific object 
	Both static and Nonstatic variables always contain the default values
	if they are not assigned with any ex. for String null, for integer 0 etc..
*/	
	
	
}
}
